BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:H02WKQB_oBA7Io7x1ysBo
SUMMARY:Forterra Fridays: February 2026
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260220T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:Forterra Fridays: February 2026 \n\nFriday\, Feb. 20\, 2026\, 1
	:00 pm to 3:30 pm \n\nWe’re excited to invite you to volunteer with us at 
	Duwamish Hill Preserve\, a Tukwila park providing critical wildlife habita
	t and public trails in a fairly industrial area. Join us on Friday\, Feb. 
	20\, from 1:00 to 3:30 PM\, to restore essential wildlife habitat by remov
	ing Himalayan blackberries that threaten our local native trees\, shrubs\,
	 and groundcover. Established native plants benefit local wildlife\, impro
	ve water quality\, and enhance air quality. \n\nYou will also gain valuabl
	e insights into ecological restoration and our innovative approach to land
	 conservation. We’ll start with a walk on the site and have restoration pr
	ofessionals on hand to answer questions about plants\, restoration\, the G
	reen Tukwila Partnership\, and Forterra. \n\nWhat we are doing: The Preser
	ve now includes an outdoor classroom area\, the Cultural Garden\, an enhan
	ced trail system\, and continued restoration opportunities for volunteers.
	 We’ll be removing the blackberry to ensure the trees\, shrubs\, and groun
	dcovers we planted can thrive. It’s a great opportunity to learn about For
	terra’s innovative approach to land conservation\, including its role in s
	afeguarding the Duwamish Hill Preserve. \n\nWhat to bring: Please dress fo
	r the weather \\(layers to stay warm/dry\\). Snacks\, drinks\, tools\, and
	 gloves will be provided. \n\nWhere to park: Park in the nearby parking lo
	t at Duwamish Hill Preserve. Signs direct you from the parking lot to wher
	e we will meet.\n\n \n\nDate and Time: Friday\, Feb. 20\, 2026\, 1:00 –3:3
	0 PM  \n\nRegister and learn more here.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/forterra-fridays-february
	-2026/17979517/2026-02-20T00
LOCATION:Duwamish Hill Preserve\, 3800 South 115th Street\, Tukwila\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:wsaqbQgQ3NcVdarSTiTdt
SUMMARY:HLF's 400-Hour Trauma-Informed Yoga & Mindfulness Certification Pro
	gram
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260221T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Holistic Life Foundation: 400-Hour Trauma-Informed Yoga & Mindf
	ulness Certification 📅 Feb 2- 22\, 2026 📍 Hotel Interurban\, Seattle\n\nTh
	e Holistic Life Foundation—a nationally recognized\, BIPOC-led nonprofit—i
	nvites you to an immersive in-person retreat in Seattle as part of its acc
	laimed 400-Hour Trauma-Informed Yoga & Mindfulness Certification Program.\
	n\nThis expert-led training combines a weekend retreat with interactive on
	line coursework\, equipping participants with the skills to teach yoga\, m
	editation\, breathwork\, and trauma-informed practices in schools\, wellne
	ss spaces\, and underserved communities.\n\nBacked by research from Johns 
	Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health\, Penn State\, and Kennedy Krieg
	er\, their programs have shown to improve emotional regulation\, reduce st
	ress\, and foster resilience. To date\, HLF has impacted over 200\,000 peo
	ple worldwide and helped establish Baltimore as the nation’s first trauma-
	informed city.\n\nJoin a movement that’s reshaping how we heal and connect
	—one breath at a time.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/hlf-s-400-hour-trauma-inf
	ormed-yoga-mindfulness-certification-program/16583260/2026-02-21T00
LOCATION:Hotel Interurban\, 223 Andover Park E\, Tukwila\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0xGyQ8zrE4XpCW6Ms0xk-
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Clarke Beach Park
DTSTAMP:20260214T003547Z
DTSTART:20260221T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Clarke Beach Park Work Party\n\nHelp us remove weeds and spre a
	d mulch in Clarke Beach Park. Weeds make it harder for native plants to g 
	row by overcrowding them and outcompeting them for resources. We want to p
	 rotect the native plants that are in the park! Once we remove the weeds\,
	 we'll spread a layer of mulch to cover the bare ground. Mulch is an incre
	d ible resource for degraded environments. It helps with weed suppression\
	, water retention\, and to create healthier soil.\n\nAll ages welcome\, no
	 experience required. Gloves\, tools\, and small snacks provided. \n\nPlea
	se note: we require participants aged 14 and under to volunteer with a p a
	rent or guardian at a ratio of 1 adult to 3 kids.\n\nWhen: Saturday\, Febr
	uary 21st\, 10am-1pm\n\nWhere: Clarke Beach Park \n\nWhat to bring: Dress 
	for the weather in clothes you don't mind getting dirty \\(think: long pan
	ts\, boots or sneakers\\). Bring water. Small snacks\, gloves\, and tools 
	will be provided.\n\nRegistration: https://volunteersignup.org/7CADJ
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-clarke-
	beach-park/18066404/2026-02-21T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
